descr: "The Measure resource provides the definition of a quality measure."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a Measure resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this measure when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this measure is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the measure. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: _url
fields.descr: "Extensions for url"

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this measure when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance."

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the measure when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the measure author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence. To provide a version consistent with the Decision Support Service specification, use the format Major.Minor.Revision (e.g. 1.0.0). For more information on versioning knowledge assets, refer to the Decision Support Service specification. Note that a version is required for non-experimental active artifacts."

fields.name: _version
fields.descr: "Extensions for version"

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the measure. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: _name
fields.descr: "Extensions for name"

fields.name: title
fields.descr: "A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the measure."

fields.name: _title
fields.descr: "Extensions for title"

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this measure. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: _status
fields.descr: "Extensions for status"

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this measure is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: _experimental
fields.descr: "Extensions for experimental"

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the measure was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the measure changes."

fields.name: _date
fields.descr: "Extensions for date"

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the measure."

fields.name: _publisher
fields.descr: "Extensions for publisher"

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the measure from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: _description
fields.descr: "Extensions for description"

fields.name: purpose
fields.descr: "Explaination of why this measure is needed and why it has been designed as it has."

fields.name: _purpose
fields.descr: "Extensions for purpose"

fields.name: usage
fields.descr: "A detailed description of how the measure is used from a clinical perspective."

fields.name: _usage
fields.descr: "Extensions for usage"

fields.name: approvalDate
fields.descr: "The date on which the resource content was approved by the publisher. Approval happens once when the content is officially approved for usage."

fields.name: _approvalDate
fields.descr: "Extensions for approvalDate"

fields.name: lastReviewDate
fields.descr: "The date on which the resource content was last reviewed. Review happens periodically after approval, but doesn't change the original approval date."

fields.name: _lastReviewDate
fields.descr: "Extensions for lastReviewDate"

fields.name: effectivePeriod
fields.descr: "The period during which the measure content was or is planned to be in active use."

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate measure instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the measure is intended to be used."

fields.name: topic
fields.descr: "Descriptive topics related to the content of the measure. Topics provide a high-level categorization of the type of the measure that can be useful for filtering and searching."

fields.name: contributor
fields.descr: "A contributor to the content of the measure, including authors, editors, reviewers, and endorsers."

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: copyright
fields.descr: "A copyright statement relating to the measure and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the measure."

fields.name: _copyright
fields.descr: "Extensions for copyright"

fields.name: relatedArtifact
fields.descr: "Related artifacts such as additional documentation, justification, or bibliographic references."

fields.name: library
fields.descr: "A reference to a Library resource containing the formal logic used by the measure."

fields.name: disclaimer
fields.descr: "Notices and disclaimers regarding the use of the measure, or related to intellectual property (such as code systems) referenced by the measure."

fields.name: _disclaimer
fields.descr: "Extensions for disclaimer"

fields.name: scoring
fields.descr: "Indicates how the calculation is performed for the measure, including proportion, ratio, continuous variable, and cohort. The value set is extensible, allowing additional measure scoring types to be represented."

fields.name: compositeScoring
fields.descr: "If this is a composite measure, the scoring method used to combine the component measures to determine the composite score."

fields.name: type
fields.descr: "Indicates whether the measure is used to examine a process, an outcome over time, a patient-reported outcome, or a structure measure such as utilization."

fields.name: riskAdjustment
fields.descr: "A description of the risk adjustment factors that may impact the resulting score for the measure and how they may be accounted for when computing and reporting measure results."

fields.name: _riskAdjustment
fields.descr: "Extensions for riskAdjustment"

fields.name: rateAggregation
fields.descr: "Describes how to combine the information calculated, based on logic in each of several populations, into one summarized result."

fields.name: _rateAggregation
fields.descr: "Extensions for rateAggregation"

fields.name: rationale
fields.descr: "Provides a succint statement of the need for the measure. Usually includes statements pertaining to importance criterion: impact, gap in care, and evidence."

fields.name: _rationale
fields.descr: "Extensions for rationale"

fields.name: clinicalRecommendationStatement
fields.descr: "Provides a summary of relevant clinical guidelines or other clinical recommendations supporting the measure."

fields.name: _clinicalRecommendationStatement
fields.descr: "Extensions for clinicalRecommendationStatement"

fields.name: improvementNotation
fields.descr: "Information on whether an increase or decrease in score is the preferred result (e.g., a higher score indicates better quality OR a lower score indicates better quality OR quality is whthin a range)."

fields.name: _improvementNotation
fields.descr: "Extensions for improvementNotation"

fields.name: definition
fields.descr: "Provides a description of an individual term used within the measure."

fields.name: _definition
fields.descr: "Extensions for definition"

fields.name: guidance
fields.descr: "Additional guidance for the measure including how it can be used in a clinical context, and the intent of the measure."

fields.name: _guidance
fields.descr: "Extensions for guidance"

fields.name: set
fields.descr: "The measure set, e.g. Preventive Care and Screening."

fields.name: _set
fields.descr: "Extensions for set"

fields.name: group
fields.descr: "A group of population criteria for the measure."

fields.name: supplementalData
fields.descr: "The supplemental data criteria for the measure report, specified as either the name of a valid CQL expression within a referenced library, or a valid FHIR Resource Path."
